1. Regularization

  • 6.1 LASSO
  • 6.2 Non-normal \(y\)

6.1 LASSO

  • Linear regression

    \[ y_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_{1,i} + \cdots + \beta_p x_{p,i} + \epsilon_i, \quad \epsilon_i \sim N(0,\sigma^2) \quad (i = 1,2,...,n) \] \[ {\mathbf y} = X{\boldsymbol\beta} + {\boldsymbol\epsilon},\quad {\boldsymbol\epsilon}\sim N({\mathbf 0}_n, \sigma^2 I_n) \]

  • \({\boldsymbol\beta}\)

    \[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta} = (X^\top X)^{-1} X^\top {\mathbf y} \]

    • \(\| {\mathbf y} - X{\boldsymbol\beta} \|_2^2\)

    • : BLUE (best linear unbiased estimator)

    • \(p\)

    • , \(X^\top X\)

  • Ridge regression

    \[ \hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\sf ridge} = (X^\top X + \lambda I)^{-1}X^\top{\mathbf y} \]

    • shrink bias

    • solution . ,

    \[ \hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\sf ridge} =\arg\min_{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\left\{ \| {\mathbf y} - X{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 + \lambda \|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 \right\} \]

  • LASSO (least absolute shrinkage and selection operator)

    • ridge (\({\mathcal L}_1\)) \[ \hat{\boldsymbol{\beta}}_{\sf lasso} =\arg\min_{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\left\{ \| {\mathbf y} - X{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_2^2 + \lambda \|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_1 \right\} \]

    • \(\boldsymbol\beta\) convex

    • \(\lambda\)

      • (crossvalidation)

    • \[ \hat{\boldsymbol\beta}_{\sf lasso} =\arg\min_{\boldsymbol\beta}\| {\mathbf y} - X{\boldsymbol\beta}\|_2^2 \] subject to \[ \|{\boldsymbol{\beta}}\|_1 \le R \] for \(R>0\)

Example:

  • Variables: \((y, x_1, x_2, ..., x_{100})\)

  • DGP: \(y = 10 + 1\times x_1 + 2\times x_2 + ... + 5\times x_5 + \epsilon\), \(\epsilon\sim N(0, 0.15^2)\). \(x_6\) ~ \(x_{100}\) \(y\) .

  • \(n = 50\). .

library(glmnet)
## Loading required package: Matrix
## Loading required package: foreach
## Loaded glmnet 2.0-16
set.seed(0)
n <- 50
p <- 100

sigma <- 0.25
beta <- c(1:5, rep(0, p - 5))

x <- cbind(matrix(runif(n*p), n, p))
y <- 10 + as.vector(x%*%beta) + sigma*rnorm(n)

fit <- glmnet(x, y)
plot(fit, xvar = "lambda", label = TRUE)

cvfit <- cv.glmnet(x, y)
plot(cvfit)

print(s <- cvfit$lambda.min)
## [1] 0.02287961
print(beta.hat <- coef(cvfit, s = "lambda.min"))

Elastic-net

  • \({\mathcal L}_1\)-norm \({\mathcal L}_2\)-norm \[ \frac{1 - \alpha}{2} \|\boldsymbol\beta \|_2^2 + \alpha \|\boldsymbol\beta\|_1 \]

  • \(\alpha = 0\) ridge regression, \(\alpha = 1\) lasso regression 

fit <- glmnet(x, y, alpha = .5)
plot(fit, xvar = "lambda", label = TRUE)

cvfit <- cv.glmnet(x, y, alpha = .5)
plot(cvfit)

print(cvfit$lambda.min)
## [1] 0.04575923
print(s <- cvfit$lambda.min)
## [1] 0.04575923
plot(y, pred.lasso, xlab = "Actual", ylab = "Predicted")
abline(0, 1, col = 2, lty = 2)
points(y, predict(fit, newx = x, s = s), col = 3, pch = "E")
